  'parenting-faq',
  'is-it-safe-to-sleep-on-your-back-during-pregnancy',
  'Is it safe to sleep on your back during pregnancy?',
  'Back-sleeping in later pregnancy can feel uncomfortable for a reason. Why side-sleeping (especially the left) is usually recommended from the second half.',
  'Why side-sleeping is usually recommended later in pregnancy — and how to make it comfortable.',
  'In early pregnancy, sleep in whatever position feels comfortable. From around the middle of pregnancy onward, many doctors suggest favouring your side rather than your back.

## Why side-sleeping?

As your bump grows, lying flat on your back can press on a major blood vessel and feel uncomfortable or light-headed. Sleeping on your side — the left is often suggested — keeps blood flowing comfortably to you and your baby.

## Making it comfortable

- Tuck a pillow between your knees and under your bump.
- If you wake on your back, simply roll back to your side — no need to worry.

> Note: ParentVeda offers gentle, evidence-informed guidance — not medical advice. Always check with your doctor for decisions about your pregnancy.',
